<title>MEXICO: Cemex says gets $600 mln revolving credit.</title>
<headline>Cemex says gets $600 mln revolving credit.</headline>
<dateline>MONTERREY, Mexico 1997-05-09</dateline>
<text>
<p>Mexican cement maker Cemex SA de CV said on Friday it had obtained a $600 revolving credit line at a maturity of three years and a rate of Libor plus 125 basis points.</p>
<p>&quot;The syndication process has been completed and will be signed on Thursday next week with all the banks in New York,&quot; said Cemex chief financial officer Rodrigo Trevino in a meeting with brokerages in the northern Mexico industrial city of Monterrey.</p>
